You are a senior full-stack engineer and system designer.

Build a production-ready Meeting Room Booking Application with AI-powered features.

Tech Stack:

* Frontend: React.js + Material UI (MUI) + PWA support
* Backend: Node.js + Express.js
* Database: MongoDB (with Mongoose)
* AI Integration:

  * Primary: Ollama (local LLM)
  * Fallback: ChatGPT API

Core Requirements:

1. The system must support dynamic meeting rooms (start with 3 but scalable to 100+)
2. Users should be able to:

   * View available rooms
   * Book time slots
   * Prevent overlapping bookings (strict conflict handling)
3. Admin should be able to:

   * Create, update, delete rooms
   * Enable/disable rooms
4. AI-based booking:

   * Accept natural language input like:
     "Book a room for 5 people tomorrow at 3 PM for 1 hour"
   * Parse input into structured booking data
   * Suggest best available room based on:

     * capacity
     * availability
     * optimal utilization (smallest fitting room)

Architecture:

* Use a modular monorepo structure:
  /client (React app)
  /server (Node API)
  /ai-service (LLM integration)
* Follow clean architecture and separation of concerns

Backend Requirements:

* Create REST APIs:

  * GET /rooms
  * POST /rooms
  * PUT /rooms/:id
  * DELETE /rooms/:id
  * POST /bookings
  * GET /bookings
  * POST /ai-bookings
* Implement booking conflict detection:
  A booking conflicts if:
  existing.start < new.end AND existing.end > new.start
* Add MongoDB indexes:
  { room_id: 1, start_time: 1, end_time: 1 }

Frontend Requirements:

* Build responsive UI using MUI
* Pages:

  * Dashboard (room list + availability)
  * Booking page (date/time picker)
  * Admin panel (room management)
* Add AI input box for natural language booking
* Use reusable components and proper state management

AI Service Requirements:

* Create a service to:

  * Call Ollama API locally
  * Extract structured booking info (people, date, time, duration)
  * Fallback to ChatGPT API if Ollama fails
* Ensure response is always valid JSON

Additional Features:

* Role-based access (user/admin)
* Basic validation and error handling
* Clean and readable code (no unnecessary complexity)

DevOps:

* Provide Docker setup:

  * MongoDB
  * Node server
  * React client
  * Ollama
* Include environment configuration (.env)

Output Requirements:
Generate:

1. Complete folder structure
2. Backend code (models, routes, controllers)
3. Frontend code (components, pages, API integration)
4. AI service implementation
5. Docker setup (docker-compose.yml)
6. Sample API requests
7. Instructions to run the project locally

Code Quality:

* Use modern JavaScript (ES6+)
* Follow best practices
* Keep code modular and scalable
* Avoid hardcoding rooms or data

Important:
Do not generate placeholder pseudo-code.
Generate real, working, production-style code.
